  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis power-law damage accumulation model employed in this package is described and validated against erythrocyte fragility data in the primary methodological reference cited via referencesIdentifier; that reference underpins the acceptanceCriteria thresholds used across multiple credibility factors herein.",
